I have a lot of respect for Steve Vai's talent and his work with so many other musicians. 

Imo, when it comes to his solo work, he is part of a particular group of guitarists I can't get down with. Technical ability and general wankery feels like the priority and songwriting (both for guitar, and overall) seems to take a backseat. There's no soul to the performance. It doesn't evoke any emotion or reaction from me aside from "Yeah, that dude is really good at guitar". It just feels like some of these players go out and just jack off with their guitar-dicks and call it a day. I'm happy to provide more members of this group upon request. 

I'm sure there's some irony here in that many would probably say some of my favorite players do similar things in a "noodly" type of way.

Anyway +1 participation trophy because Steve definitely is talented AF

That's my hot take, musicians and non-musicians alike, feel free to roast me for it.
